  "_comment_splash_tips": "Splash screen tips — shown one at a time with prev/next navigation",
  "splashTip01": "To customize the sizing to your measurements, update Thread Properties in Options menu.",
  "splashTip02": "The notation field understands repeats — try r: 4x(3ds-p) instead of writing it out.",
  "splashTip03": "Zoom with Shift + Scroll Wheel; hold Space and drag to pan without switching tools.",
  "splashTip04": "Order numbers follow your thread path — number elements in the sequence you'll tat them.",
  "splashTip05": "Materials carry color and gradient settings — change one material to update all linked elements.",
  "splashTip06": "Polar Array (Arrange menu) places N copies at equal angles around a grid center automatically.",
  "splashTip07": "Picot length affects design: there are short (sp), regular (p) and long picots (lp) available.",
  "splashTip08": "Split rings have independent A and B notation — the two stitch counts don't need to match.",
  "splashTip09": "Press Escape repeatedly to walk back through modes to a safe deselected state.",
  "splashTip10": "The Ruler tool reads in millimetres — set DS width in Thread Properties first for accuracy.",
  "splashTip11": "Picots can be tricky: joint picots (jp), guided joint picots (jpg), and guide points (gp) are all different.",
  "splashTip12": "Realistic mode shows stitches in detail — it can be slow on large patterns, give it a moment to render.",
  "splashTip13": "Name your polar grids in the panel — they are global for all your projects.",
  "splashTip14": "Save all your projects in one folder — TattingCAD builds a visual recent projects browser.",
  "splashTip15": "Export SVG then open it in a vector program (like Inkscape) to save as PNG/JPG at any size.",
